{
  "text": "Previous work in this area has been done in [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] and [CITATION_3] . [CITATION_4] examines the design of an optimisation methodology that uses its own split masking method as an alternative reduced energy consumption masking countermeasure for an embedded device. [CITATION_5] proposes a masking method based on an increased number of lookup tables to provide a more energy efficient masking method against higher order attacks. This work focuses on the design of its own type of masking aimed at reducing the energy consumption overhead at the expense of other factors (such as memory in [CITATION_6] ).",
